data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime.** There is no workaround.

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider let you opt back into sync-over-async. **EF Core 11 removes that opt-in entirely** — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`, etc. now always throw when used with the Cosmos provider.

You must convert every method to its async equivalent:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- This is a **medium-impact** breaking change (EF Core issue [#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059))
- The change cascades — all callers up the chain must become `async`/`await` too
- Any repository interfaces will need updated signatures returning `Task<T>`
